Yes! Baylor University has many notable alumni in a variety of fields. Here are a few examples:

1. Robert Griffin III: NFL quarterback and Heisman Trophy winner 

2. Brittany Howard: Lead singer and guitarist of the band Alabama Shakes

3. Karen W. Jonas: Country music singer and songwriter

4. Bear Grylls: Adventurer, TV personality, and author 

5. Angela Kinsey: Actress known for her role on the TV show "The Office"

6. David Crowder: Contemporary Christian musician 

7. Jennifer Garner: Actress known for her roles in movies such as "13 Going on 30" and "Dallas Buyers Club"

8. Jim Nantz: Sportscaster for CBS Sports 

9. Trey Wingo: Sportscaster and TV personality 

10. Thomas Harris: Author of the popular thriller novel "The Silence of the Lambs"

These are just a few examples of the many successful Baylor University alumni.
